# <%= projectName %> — System Design

## Overview

This is a **multi-microservice monorepo**. Each service owns its own
Postgres database, Redis cache, backend image, and deployment lifecycle.
The `auth` service is the trust anchor; every other service verifies
requests by forwarding the user's cookie to it.

```
    ┌─────────────────────────────┐
    │        clients              │
    │  (web, mobile — per svc)    │
    └──────────────┬──────────────┘
                   │
                   │  session cookie (BetterAuth)
                   ▼
    ┌─────────────────────────────┐
    │        auth service         │
    │   BetterAuth │ DB │ Redis   │
    │   users, sessions, OAuth    │
    └──────────────▲──────────────┘
                   │
                   │  cookie forward
                   │  /api/auth/get-session
                   │
    ┌─────────────────────────────┐
    │       base services         │
    │                             │
    │   <%= services.filter((s) => s.kind !== 'auth').map((s) => s.name).join(', ') %>
    │                             │
    │   (each owns its own DB     │
    │    and Redis instance)      │
    └─────────────────────────────┘
```

