## Security boundaries

- Never trust client input — validate everything server-side with
  TypeBox schemas.
- Session tokens are httpOnly cookies, issued and rotated by
  BetterAuth inside the `auth` service.
- All database operations use parameterized queries
  (<%= orm.charAt(0).toUpperCase() + orm.slice(1) %>).
- Non-auth services must forward cookies to the auth service for
  every protected route — never short-circuit by trusting a header
  or client-supplied user ID.

## stackr.config.json

`stackr.config.json` in the repository root is the source of truth for
which services exist, which ports they use, which auth middleware
flavor they run, and which integrations they ship with. Phase 3's
`stackr add service` reads and updates this file.

Never edit `stackr.config.json` by hand to add a service — the
`docker-compose.yml` and per-service `backend/package.json` will get
out of sync. Always use `stackr add service <name>`.
